subSubSection.paragraph:
Legs long, slender, setose (
Fig. 3
). All femora robust, broadening towards apex. Tibiae slender, at most half of femora width, lacking longitudinal grooves or carinae, with two apical spurs shorter than basal tarsomere. All tarsi 5-segmented. Tarsomere 5 longer, as long or slightly longer than tarsi 1–4 together, basal 4 tarsomeres each with a group of erect setae at apex. Claws simple.
